      "section": [
        "Niyok"
      ],
      "text": "Niyok was the sister of Nutha and a friend of Katara's from the Southern Water Tribe. In order to find a job and make a living, she and her sister left the tribe for the Earth Kingdom, where they were hired to work at the Earthen Fire Refinery."
    },
    {
      "body": "Niyok was born and raised in the Southern Water Tribe. Sometime before 102 ${link_0}, she moved to work at the Earthen Fire Refinery in the Earth Kingdom.",
      "links": [
        {
          "body": "AG",
          "key": "${link_0}",
          "target": {
            "external": false,
            "href": "/wiki/History_of_the_World_of_Avatar#Dates",
            "page": "History_of_the_World_of_Avatar"
          }
        }
      ],
      "section": [
        "Niyok",
        "History"
      ],
      "text": "Niyok was born and raised in the Southern Water Tribe. Sometime before 102 AG, she moved to work at the Earthen Fire Refinery in the Earth Kingdom."
    },
    {
      "body": "One day, Niyok spotted Katara walking with ${link_0} ${link_1}, ${link_2}, and three ${link_3}, ${link_4}, ${link_5}, and ${link_6}. She caught Katara's attention and happily embraced the ${link_7}, whom she had not seen since Katara's departure from the tribe with Aang years prior. Upon inquiry, she explained that she had traveled to the Earth Kingdom in order to work at the refinery. Their reunion was cut short, however, when ${link_8} gave Katara a noncommittal stare and called Niyok back over to where she and another friend were sitting.",
      "links": [
